message.content: cs.RO, cs.BIO, cs.HC, cs.ME, cs.NEURON - The paper describes the design and development of a robotic glove for hand rehabilitation, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and bio-inspired design (cs.BIO). The glove is intended for use in healthcare (cs.HC) and involves mechanical engineering (cs.ME) in its fabrication. The system also involves the use of sEMG signals to train the assistive glove, which involves neural networks (cs.NEURON).
